item.title: lost boys
item.dc:creator: eccchobunny
item.description: Installation, databending 11.10. 2017     Memorial piece to my friends who died of self infliction due to conditions we are living in that led them there. They were all mostly around 21 years old. All male friends as well, and I say this to bring up the fact that men are more likely to be succesful in a suicidal attempt and more likely to have issues with addictions. Part of the reason they end up there is because of the pressure put on men to be “successful” in life and to not share their feelings. This is intertwined with the fact that mental healthcare is hard to access in america for many people and particularly so if you are poor and working class. We need to address these intersectional subjects in order to curb the rising suicide and overdose rates. Those are some surface level symptoms of the disease that is capitalism and patriarchal masculinity

item.title: dream log
item.dc:creator: eccchobunny
item.description: Arduino, muscle sensor, Processing, prints12.14. 2017     Hooked a muscle sensor up to my eyelid while sleeping for a few nights that was connected to a piece of code I wrote that would use the sensors data to draw the circles. The more widespread the circles, the more my eyelids were moving indicating dreaming. I decided to make prints with both the numerical data and the drawings together as I felt it looked cryptic in the way that dreams can be.

item.title: untitled memorial
item.dc:creator: eccchobunny
item.description: Lamb skull, fairy lights, glittery foliage and EL wire 05.09. 2018     Memorial piece to my friends lost to deaths of despair. The El wire is shaped into hand positions held by Buddah and gesture an expelling of demons, sprinkling of immortality(in the way that they will never be forgotton) and a blessing of protection (“do not fear”). Elements of Buddhism helped me a lot to get through experiencing those deaths
